posts.title: Saturday 5th January, 2019
posts.content:
• Eggs for breakfast this morning, our usual weekend tradition (although - we had to ration our dwindling supply of toast)
  • After, we left to drive to Toowoomba
  • At Toowoomba we went to an organic cafe and Julie got a coffee, and AJ a smooth - it was expensive, but nice. I left them a google review.
  • We then drove over to pickup the sim racing seat and wheel - Fanatec GT3 RS
  • The seat was too big to fit into the car - we had to split it in half to get it in
  • After, we took AJ to Queens park where we played. 
  • He loved the merry-go-round. It was his first time on one.
  • After the park we went hunting for a bakery - the first one was closed, but the second open
  • Julie and I had pies for lunch, AJ didn't really eat his sausage roll - but we all shared a jam doughnut 
  • We jumped back into the car and drove back to Brisbane, calling mum to meet her at our place
  • Mum and Tim came over - Tim stayed, while Mum and I left to look at cars for her (Convertible 2 series BMW's)
  • First we looked at a black on at a Jaguar dealer at Newstead - it was fine, but I hated the black color and it had been kept OK
  • We then drove to a spa (On Eagles Wings) at the Gold Coast hinterland to see the other car, which was much nicer.
  • Mum and I  had a tea/coffee together to discuss - then negotiated and agreed to a price to buy the car
  • We drove back to Brisbane, where I searched and found the car written off - so we called and cancelled the sale.
  • Mum looked after AJ, and Julie and I went out
  • We had Burgers and Ribs at James St, then went for a walk and had Magnum ice creams
  • Finally, we came home - said goodbye to Mum & Tim, then crashed out to sleep

posts.title: Sunday 6th January, 2019
posts.content:
• Regular breakfast today - no eggs this weekend as we were all out of bread
  • We got ready, and started our drive up to the Noosa Habitat camp grounds
  • I tried to read my book on Agile PM on the way up (on the tablet), but AJ was quite unsettled and kept needing my attention
  • I fed AJ throughout the drive - mostly little potato style balls we took from our plane trip back to Brisbane earlier in the week
  • We stopped at Yandina IGA for supplies - we got a box of Split ice cream, and I bought AJ a hot wheels car (R34 GTR)
  • We kept driving and made it to habitat - which needed us to drive down a long dirt road to get there
  • Arriving, we sat near the water with Andy, Laticha, John, Sally, Therese, and Justine - enjoying our ice creams shortly after arriving.
  • We moved our gear to be under a better patch of shade, then had more of Tich's birthday cake
  • AJ got changed into his swim wear, then we took him into the water which was incredibly shallow - and allowed him to walk out far
  • He loved independently playing in the water, although Julie kept on getting worried
  • We walked out some distance - then walked back to sit around the shoreline under the shade of trees, while AJ played in the shallows with rocks
  • He put a few in his mouth - not sure if he ate one or not
  • After a while we picked him up to leave - and he was covered in liquid poo
  • I managed to clean him and I up, although my singlet got poo juice on it and we washed it - trying later to dry it out the window of our car
  • We drove to Dad and Tiziana's house - getting KFC on the way for a very late lunch
  • There, AJ got his Christmas presents from them - and we found presents from Danyal & Louise
  • We stayed for some time - with AJ saying "Nonna" for the first time
  • Arriving at home, we got AJ ready for bed - and I left for a run
  • The run was 13.5km, first long run of the year towards my marathon target
  • I got home, had a shower, and we watched two episodes of Seinfeld in bed before going to sleep

Soon we put him to bed, then I booked my accommodation for Dave's wedding in the UK on airbnb at Blagdon.
Called mum and checked on her, confirming her birthday lunch plans and her thoughts on a new car.
Went to bed and read more of Managing Projects with Agile - before Julie came home and we slept.

posts.title: Friday 11th January, 2019
posts.content:

Had a relaxed day, David was sick - and my day was focused on our carrier initiative and revisiting the cross-functional strategy (putting the Magento dev's into the teams).

Played pool with Marlsey and chatted, then finished the day with meetings before skipping the team pub session (no fun when you're not drinking), and went to the gym.

First dead lift session for the year, did a relaxed 120kg 5x5 (although had to hook grip it... which was annoying), and mixed in overheads/clean-and-jerk and some kettlebells. My wrist straps kept falling apart, so I stopped early with the clean-and-jerk's and threw my straps away on the way out.

Walked home, listened to Freakonomics on Yang's run for the 2020 US President and his opinions and observations on the US economy.

Got home - convinced Julie of take-out so went down to the urban village and tried the Chinese place there. They seemed to forget one of the dishes, but quickly cooked it and I got out of there in 30mins or so. It was a good Char Kway Teow (i've been looking for one), so I was pretty stoked I found one so good, so close to home.

Watched Seinfeld as we ate (Cadillac episode, followed by the Marissa Tomey episode) - before heading to beg to play Dark Souls. Made it mostly through The Dukes Archive to the bonfire, and called it a night.

I drove back to Kelvin Grove to the barber in the urban village near the butcher. I think the guys were Turkish, but either way - the hair cut was really good.

We left the park and went straight to Jas and Laughy's unit, and swam. AJ was ridiculously excited to swim, and extremely upset when we took him away from the pool.

I grabbed fish and chips for us all from Caraway Pier at the urban village, and after what was a very messy meal we went home and I put AJ to bed.

Julie had an early night, and I stayed up on the PC.
